UAV-300P. Specifications. A photo.
UAV-300P - unmanned aerial vehicle developed by the Ukrainian company "Poltava Aero Club". The device is designed for reconnaissance and observation tasks, can be used in various fields such as agriculture, forestry, environmental monitoring, etc.
The UAV-300P has a compact size, which makes it easy to transport and deploy in remote locations. The device is equipped with a camera that allows you to capture high-quality images and video, which can be used for various purposes.
The power plant of the UAV-300P is represented by a gasoline engine, which provides the device with a maximum speed of 150 km / h, with a flight duration of up to 4 hours. The maximum range of the drone is 150 kilometers.
Specifications UAV-300P:
Maximum takeoff weight: 25 kg;
Flight duration: 4 hours;
Maximum speed: 150 km / h;
Range: 150 km;
Camera resolution: 12 MP;
Dimensions of the UAV: 3.6 m x 0.7 m x 0.8 m (folded);
Wingspan: 4.5 meters.
Photography and video shooting is carried out using a high-resolution camera with a resolution of 12 MP, which allows you to capture clear and detailed images and videos. The device also has a built-in GPS and GLONASS navigation systems that allow you to accurately determine the location of the drone during flight.
UAV-300P is equipped with a ground control station, which allows you to remotely control the device and monitor its operation in real time. The device can be controlled using a wireless connection or a wired connection.
